reviewText:
Early Access Review

////NEW REVIEW////

Went on to Youtube and watched some playthroughs/tutorials on this game.  Initially I was very frustrated (see below), but, after watching the walkthroughs, I have a better understanding/respect as to how this game is played and, indeed, how clever it is.  I've began playing it again and am enjoying it very much.  That said, I would like to see more opportunities/means to acquire resources and incentive for playing rather than waiting.  The current means is by waiting, challenging other players or the AI, or, defending your base.  However the rewards through playing, initially, were around 7K for supplies and gas but, taper off to around 2K.  Overall though, this game is growing on me more and more.

////OLD REVIEW////

You'll play this game initially and think wow, awesome, and amazing.  However, as you try to build up your base, forces, and get your feet wet, you'll have a higher level player stomp you....  I'm not sure if some of the other players experienced this, but, I found during one base defense mission, that I threw my entire range of forces at one tank and it took little to no damage and all my infantry and tanks died quickly.  The emplacements offered nothing in terms of resistance as well, dying in one to two hits.  Must have been Rambo manning the tank....  Point being, attackers took little to no damage and were at 100% force strength when he took out my base.

Good idea/concept.  Once the developers work out the hacks, bugs, and players who cheat, it will be a good game.  For now, though, this game still is a ways off from being anywhere near balanced or playable.  Feel free to hit me up with any questions.  Cheers
